<plot>Shalom and welcome to the Jewish quarters of Brooklyn. Hosted by Pearl Gluck, director of the critically acclaimed feature documentary "Divan", this fascinating walk through Brooklyn's famed clandestine Hasidic community will give you the opportunity to see their customs up close and personal. Taste their delicious motzah ball soup, dress in their garments, visit the butcher, and exchange courteous views with a rabbi. Lichaim.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?657500</url></doc>
